" For our inaugural post, we are pleased to present part one of our conversation with Linus Torvalds, creator of the Linux Operating System and fellow at the Linux Foundation.

We have broken the conversation with Linus into two parts." [http://linux-foundation.org/weblogs/openvoices/2008/01/07/welcome-to-open-voices/] 

Linus comments on a variety of topics including patents, internal and external competition, the broader adoption of Linux, Microsoft and much more."
